def: Cupel dust. [Obs.]Powder of steel, or copple dust. Bacon.
To fashion anew; to form or mold into shape a second time.MacKnight.
The art of measuring degrees of heat, or the expansion ofbodies by heat.
Containing many nuclei; as, multinuclear cells.
A tea cake slighty sweetened, and raised with yeast, baked inthe form of biscuits or in a thin loaf, and eaten hot with butter.

An electro-negative element or radical, which, by combinationwith a metal, forms a haloid salt; especially, chlorine, bromine, andiodine; sometimes, also, fluorine and cyanogen. See Chlorine family,under Chlorine.
The cry of cats; a harsh, disagreeable noise or cry like thecry of cats. Shak.
Having the form of an ax hatchet.
